{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, for solar irradiation forecasting, a novel approach combining Gramian Angular Field and Convolutional LSTM networks has shown improved forecasting performance despite using a small dataset [19].",
    "A hybrid approach that integrates machine learning techniques with statistical methods has also been suggested for forecasting solar power generation [20] and dissolved oxygen level prediction [21], demonstrating improved accuracy over standalone models.",
    "A combined interval forecasting method proposed in [22], which integrates three artificial intelligence models (LSTM, BiLSTM, and GRU) with a statistical model (ARIMA), leveraging interval prediction mechanisms for a reliable forecasts amidst uncertainty in wind energy generation.",
    "In the field of air quality prediction, a Markov-weighted fuzzy time-series model utilizing an optimal partitioning technique has been created for forecasting air pollution, surpassing the performance of traditional fuzzy time-series models and conventional approaches [23].",
    "Furthermore, the integration of wavelet transform with convolutional neural networks has proven effective in identifying patterns within rainfall time series, leading to satisfactory forecasting outcomes [24]."
  ]
}